Must have:

CS70, EE16AB (recommended) or Math54+110, Math53

Great to have:

EE126 or Prob140, EE127, Math 104, Math 110, Data 100

A good route for you:

Fa19: EE16A, CS70

Sp20: EE16B, Math 53

Fa20: EE126/Prob140, EE127 (or go straight into CS189)

Hi all! I am very interested in taking CS189, but have not taken Math 53 or Math 54. I took EE16A and plan to take 54 next semester. How strict/necessary are these math requirements?

Does the linear algebra in EE16A cover what's needed for 189? Is Math 53 really necessary, or can I get by with self-study of particular 53 topics? If 53 is really necessary, can it be taken concurrently?

Thank you!
